#Statistical arbitrage  is a trading strategy that emerged in the 1980s. It allows traders to profit from price discrepancies in related assets or the same asset but on different  trading platforms.
The approach for this project is based on the idea that the market occasionally misprices in regards to crypto assets due to supply and demand, market inefficiences and human error all due to economic impact and or incorrect valuation methods.
With that being said, for this project these discrepancies will be exploited using statistical arbitrage methods that yield profitability.

#Objective of Project: In the cryptocurrency market find and exammine pricing inefficiencies for crypto pairs using specific statistical arbitrage strategies such as momental and reversal that yield profits.

# %matplotlib inline  

from pycoingecko import CoinGeckoAPI
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import time

# -------- Settings ----------
VS_CCY = "usd"
COINS = ["bitcoin", "ethereum", "tether", "dogecoin", "shiba-inu", "litecoin"]
DAYS = 365
SLEEP = 1.0
# ----------------------------

cg = CoinGeckoAPI()

def fetch_chart(coin_id):
    try:
        return cg.get_coin_market_chart(id=coin_id, vs_currency=VS_CCY, days=DAYS)
    except AttributeError:
        return cg.get_coin_market_chart_by_id(id=coin_id, vs_currency=VS_CCY, days=DAYS)

# 1) Collect data
all_data = pd.DataFrame()

for coin in COINS:
    print(f"Fetching {coin}...")
    data = fetch_chart(coin)
    prices = pd.DataFrame(data["prices"], columns=["ts_ms", coin])
    prices["date"] = pd.to_datetime(prices["ts_ms"], unit="ms")
    prices.set_index("date", inplace=True)
    prices.drop(columns=["ts_ms"], inplace=True)
    
    if all_data.empty:
        all_data = prices
    else:
        all_data = all_data.join(prices, how="outer")
    
    time.sleep(SLEEP)

# 2) Define pairs
pairs = [
    ("bitcoin", "ethereum"),
    ("tether", "dogecoin"),
    ("shiba-inu", "litecoin")
]

# 3) Plot each pair
for c1, c2 in pairs:
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.plot(all_data.index, all_data[c1], label=c1.capitalize())
    plt.plot(all_data.index, all_data[c2], label=c2.capitalize())
    plt.title(f"{c1.capitalize()} vs {c2.capitalize()}  Price History (1 Year)")
    plt.xlabel("Date")
    plt.ylabel(f"Price ({VS_CCY.upper()})")
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid(True)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

from pycoingecko import CoinGeckoAPI
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import time

# ---------------- Settings ----------------
VS = "usd"
COINS = ["bitcoin", "ethereum", "tether", "dogecoin", "shiba-inu", "litecoin"]
DAYS = 365
SLEEP = 0.8
# Momentum params
LOOKBACK = 60                 # momentum window (days)
# Costs
COST_MARKET = 0.0020          # 20 bps
COST_LIMIT  = 0.0007          # 7 bps
# ------------------------------------------

cg = CoinGeckoAPI()

def fetch_market_chart(coin_id, vs=VS, days=DAYS):
    try:
        return cg.get_coin_market_chart(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days)
    except AttributeError:
        return cg.get_coin_market_chart_by_id(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days)

# 1) Fetch daily prices
prices = pd.DataFrame()
for coin in COINS:
    data = fetch_market_chart(coin)
    px = pd.DataFrame(data["prices"], columns=["ts_ms", coin])
    px["date"] = pd.to_datetime(px["ts_ms"], unit="ms")
    px = px.set_index("date")[[coin]]
    prices = px if prices.empty else prices.join(px, how="outer")
    time.sleep(SLEEP)

prices = prices.sort_index().ffill().dropna(how="all")

# 2) Momentum signal (price > moving average)
def momentum_position(series, lookback=LOOKBACK):
    ma = series.rolling(lookback).mean()
    pos = (series > ma).astype(float)
    return pos

positions = prices.apply(momentum_position)

# 3) Daily returns
rets = prices.pct_change().fillna(0)

# Strategy cumulative returns with costs
def strategy_return_with_costs(ret_series, pos_series, cost=0.0):
    pos_shift = pos_series.shift(1).fillna(0)
    strat_ret = pos_shift * ret_series
    trades = pos_series.diff().abs().fillna(0)
    strat_ret = strat_ret - trades * cost
    return (1 + strat_ret).prod() - 1   # total return over 1 year

# 4) Build summary DataFrame
results = []
for coin in COINS:
    results.append({
        "Coin": coin,
        "Momentum (No Cost) %": strategy_return_with_costs(rets[coin], positions[coin], 0.0) * 100,
        "Momentum (Market Cost) %": strategy_return_with_costs(rets[coin], positions[coin], COST_MARKET) * 100,
        "Momentum (Limit Cost) %": strategy_return_with_costs(rets[coin], positions[coin], COST_LIMIT) * 100,
        "Buy & Hold %": ((prices[coin].iloc[-1] / prices[coin].iloc[0]) - 1) * 100
    })

df_summary = pd.DataFrame(results).set_index("Coin").round(2)

print("\n=== 1-Year Momentum vs Buy & Hold ===")
print(df_summary)

# 5) Plot as bar chart
ax = df_summary.plot(kind="bar", figsize=(12,6))
plt.title("1-Year Momentum Strategy vs Buy & Hold")
plt.ylabel("Return (%)")
plt.grid(axis="y")
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import time

# %matplotlib inline 

import time
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pycoingecko import CoinGeckoAPI

# ================= Settings =================
COINS = ["bitcoin", "ethereum", "tether", "dogecoin", "shiba-inu", "litecoin"]
NAMES = {
    "bitcoin":"Bitcoin","ethereum":"Ethereum","tether":"Tether",
    "dogecoin":"Dogecoin","shiba-inu":"Shiba Inu","litecoin":"Litecoin"
}
PAIRS = [("bitcoin","ethereum"),
         ("tether","dogecoin"),
         ("shiba-inu","litecoin")]

VS = "usd"
DAYS = 365
SLEEP = 0.9

# Momentum (Rate-of-Change over lookback days)
MOM_LOOKBACK = 20       # try 20, 50, 100
ENTRY_MOM = 0.0         # go long when ROC > ENTRY_MOM
EXIT_MOM  = 0.0         # exit (flat) when ROC <= EXIT_MOM

# Costs per position change (enter OR exit)
COST_MARKET = 0.0020    # 20 bps (20 slippage)
COST_LIMIT  = 0.0007    # 7 bps (commission only)
# ===========================================

cg = CoinGeckoAPI()

def fetch_market_chart(coin_id, vs=VS, days=DAYS):
    """Close+Volume via CoinGecko; supports both method names across versions."""
    try:
        return cg.get_coin_market_chart(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days)
    except AttributeError:
        return cg.get_coin_market_chart_by_id(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days)

def build_ohlcv_from_market_chart(mc):
    """
    CoinGecko market_chart returns irregular timestamps:
      - 'prices' -> [ts_ms, price]
      - 'total_volumes' -> [ts_ms, volume]
    Merge and resample to daily OHLCV.
    """
    px  = pd.DataFrame(mc["prices"],        columns=["ts","price"])
    vol = pd.DataFrame(mc["total_volumes"], columns=["ts","volume"])
    df  = px.merge(vol, on="ts", how="left")
    df["date"] = pd.to_datetime(df["ts"], unit="ms")
    df = df.set_index("date").drop(columns=["ts"]).sort_index()

    ohlcv = df.resample("1D").agg({
        "price": ["first","max","min","last"],
        "volume":"sum"
    })
    ohlcv.columns = ["Open","High","Low","Close","Volume"]
    return ohlcv.dropna()

def momentum_positions(close, lb=MOM_LOOKBACK, entry=ENTRY_MOM, exit_=EXIT_MOM):
    """Long-only momentum based on Rate-of-Change (ROC)."""
    roc = close.pct_change(lb)
    pos = pd.Series(0.0, index=close.index)
    in_pos = False
    for i, r in enumerate(roc):
        if np.isnan(r):
            pos.iloc[i] = 1.0 if in_pos else 0.0
            continue
        if not in_pos and r > entry:
            in_pos = True
        elif in_pos and r <= exit_:
            in_pos = False
        pos.iloc[i] = 1.0 if in_pos else 0.0
    return pos

def equity_with_costs(rets, pos, cost_per_change):
    """Apply T-1 position to T return; charge cost on each enter/exit."""
    pos_t1 = pos.shift(1).fillna(0.0)
    strat = pos_t1 * rets
    flips = pos.diff().abs().fillna(0.0)  # 1 on enter, 1 on exit
    strat = strat - flips * cost_per_change
    eq = (1 + strat).cumprod()
    if not eq.empty:
        eq.iloc[0] = 1.0
    return eq

# ---------- RUN backtest ----------
per_coin = {}
rows = []

for cid in COINS:
    print(f"Processing {cid} ...")
    mc    = fetch_market_chart(cid); time.sleep(SLEEP)
    ohlcv = build_ohlcv_from_market_chart(mc)

    # Returns & positions
    rets = ohlcv["Close"].pct_change().fillna(0.0)
    pos  = momentum_positions(ohlcv["Close"])

    # Equities (with costs) and Buy&Hold
    eq_market = equity_with_costs(rets, pos, COST_MARKET)
    eq_limit  = equity_with_costs(rets, pos, COST_LIMIT)
    eq_bh     = (1 + rets).cumprod(); eq_bh.iloc[0] = 1.0

    per_coin[cid] = dict(eq_m=eq_market, eq_l=eq_limit, eq_bh=eq_bh)

    # Collect summary
    rows.append({
        "Coin": NAMES[cid],
        "Momentum (Market) %": round((eq_market.iloc[-1]-1)*100, 2),
        "Momentum (Limit) %":  round((eq_limit.iloc[-1]-1)*100,  2),
        "Buy & Hold %":        round((eq_bh.iloc[-1]-1)*100,     2)
    })

# ---------- Pairwise Equity Curves ----------
for c1, c2 in PAIRS:
    plt.figure(figsize=(14,6))
    # Pair A
    plt.plot(per_coin[c1]["eq_m"].index, per_coin[c1]["eq_m"], label=f"{NAMES[c1]} Mom (Market)")
    plt.plot(per_coin[c1]["eq_l"].index, per_coin[c1]["eq_l"], label=f"{NAMES[c1]} Mom (Limit)")
    plt.plot(per_coin[c1]["eq_bh"].index, per_coin[c1]["eq_bh"], "--", label=f"{NAMES[c1]} Buy&Hold")
    # Pair B
    plt.plot(per_coin[c2]["eq_m"].index, per_coin[c2]["eq_m"], label=f"{NAMES[c2]} Mom (Market)")
    plt.plot(per_coin[c2]["eq_l"].index, per_coin[c2]["eq_l"], label=f"{NAMES[c2]} Mom (Limit)")
    plt.plot(per_coin[c2]["eq_bh"].index, per_coin[c2]["eq_bh"], "--", label=f"{NAMES[c2]} Buy&Hold")

    plt.title(f"Equity Curves  Momentum vs Buy&Hold (1Y): {NAMES[c1]} & {NAMES[c2]}")
    plt.ylabel("Equity (Start=1.0)")
    plt.grid(True, alpha=0.4)
    plt.legend(ncol=3, fontsize=9)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# ---------- Summary Bar Chart ----------
summary = pd.DataFrame(rows).set_index("Coin").sort_values("Momentum (Market) %", ascending=False)
print("\n=== Momentum Backtest Summary (1Y)  Market 27bps, Limit 7bps ===")
print(summary)

ax = summary[["Momentum (Market) %","Momentum (Limit) %","Buy & Hold %"]].plot(
    kind="bar", figsize=(12,6), width=0.8
)
plt.title("Final 1Y Return  Momentum (Market vs Limit) vs Buy & Hold")
plt.ylabel("Return (%)")
plt.grid(axis="y", linestyle="--", alpha=0.6)
plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha="right")
plt.legend(title="Strategy", fontsize=10)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# %matplotlib inline 

from pycoingecko import CoinGeckoAPI
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import time

# ---------------- Settings ----------------
COINS = ["bitcoin", "ethereum", "tether", "dogecoin", "shiba-inu", "litecoin"]
PAIRS = [("bitcoin", "ethereum"),
         ("tether", "dogecoin"),
         ("shiba-inu", "litecoin")]

VS = "usd"
DAYS = 365
SLEEP = 0.9            # small delay to respect API rate limits

# Reversal params (z-score vs SMA/STD)
WINDOW  = 20           # rolling window
ENTRY_Z = -1.0         # enter when z < ENTRY_Z (oversold)
EXIT_Z  = 0.0          # exit when z >= EXIT_Z (back to normal)

# Trading costs per position change (enter or exit)
COST_MARKET = 0.0020   # 20 bps (20 bps slippage)
COST_LIMIT  = 0.0007   # 7 bps commission
# ------------------------------------------

cg = CoinGeckoAPI()

def fetch_market_chart(coin_id, vs=VS, days=DAYS):
    """Handles pycoingecko version differences."""
    try:
        return cg.get_coin_market_chart(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days)
    except AttributeError:
        return cg.get_coin_market_chart_by_id(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days)

# 1) Fetch close prices for 1Y
prices = pd.DataFrame()
for coin in COINS:
    print(f"Fetching {coin}...")
    data = fetch_market_chart(coin)
    # CoinGecko returns [timestamp_ms, price]
    px = pd.DataFrame(data["prices"], columns=["ts_ms", coin])
    px["date"] = pd.to_datetime(px["ts_ms"], unit="ms")
    px = px.set_index("date")[[coin]]
    prices = px if prices.empty else prices.join(px, how="outer")
    time.sleep(SLEEP)

# Clean and align timestamps; forward-fill occasional gaps
prices = prices.sort_index().ffill().dropna(how="all")

# 2) Build long-only reversal positions (z-score mean reversion)
def long_only_reversal_position(series, window=WINDOW, entry_z=ENTRY_Z, exit_z=EXIT_Z):
    s = series.dropna()
    sma = s.rolling(window).mean()
    sd  = s.rolling(window).std()
    z   = (s - sma) / sd

    pos = pd.Series(0.0, index=s.index)
    in_pos = False
    for i, zi in enumerate(z):
        if np.isnan(zi):
            pos.iloc[i] = 1.0 if in_pos else 0.0
            continue
        if not in_pos and zi < entry_z:
            in_pos = True
        elif in_pos and zi >= exit_z:
            in_pos = False
        pos.iloc[i] = 1.0 if in_pos else 0.0
    return pos

positions = prices.apply(long_only_reversal_position)

# 3) Daily returns
rets = prices.pct_change().fillna(0)

# 4) Strategy cumulative returns with costs on position changes
def cumulative_with_costs(ret_series, pos_series, cost_per_trade):
    # use yesterday's position to avoid look-ahead
    pos_shift = pos_series.shift(1).fillna(0)
    strat_ret = pos_shift * ret_series
    # charge cost when position flips (enter or exit)
    trades = pos_series.diff().abs().fillna(0)     # 1 on change 0->1 or 1->0
    strat_ret = strat_ret - trades * cost_per_trade
    equity = (1 + strat_ret).cumprod()
    equity.iloc[0] = 1.0
    return equity

# 5) Build equities for market-cost and limit-cost, plus Buy&Hold
cum_rev_market = pd.DataFrame(index=rets.index)
cum_rev_limit  = pd.DataFrame(index=rets.index)
buy_hold       = (prices / prices.iloc[0])  # start at 1.0

for c in COINS:
    cum_rev_market[c] = cumulative_with_costs(rets[c], positions[c], COST_MARKET)
    cum_rev_limit[c]  = cumulative_with_costs(rets[c], positions[c], COST_LIMIT)

# 6) Summary table (final 1Y returns)
rows = []
for c in COINS:
    rows.append({
        "Coin": c,
        "Reversal (Market) %": round((cum_rev_market[c].iloc[-1]-1)*100, 2),
        "Reversal (Limit) %":  round((cum_rev_limit[c].iloc[-1]-1)*100, 2),
        "Buy & Hold %":        round((buy_hold[c].iloc[-1]-1)*100, 2)
    })
summary = pd.DataFrame(rows).set_index("Coin").sort_values("Reversal (Market) %", ascending=False)

print("\n=== Reversal Backtest (1Y)  Costs: Market=27bps, Limit=7bps ===")
print(summary)

# 7) Pair charts: cumulative returns vs Buy&Hold (start at 0 on Y-axis)
for c1, c2 in PAIRS:
    plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
    # Reversal (Market)
    plt.plot(cum_rev_market.index, cum_rev_market[c1]-1, label=f"{c1} Rev (market)")
    plt.plot(cum_rev_market.index, cum_rev_market[c2]-1, label=f"{c2} Rev (market)")
    # Reversal (Limit)
    plt.plot(cum_rev_limit.index,  cum_rev_limit[c1]-1,  label=f"{c1} Rev (limit)")
    plt.plot(cum_rev_limit.index,  cum_rev_limit[c2]-1,  label=f"{c2} Rev (limit)")
    # Buy & Hold
    plt.plot(buy_hold.index,       buy_hold[c1]-1,       "--", label=f"{c1} Buy&Hold")
    plt.plot(buy_hold.index,       buy_hold[c2]-1,       "--", label=f"{c2} Buy&Hold")

    plt.title(f"Reversal vs Buy & Hold (1Y)  {c1} vs {c2}")
    plt.xlabel("Date")
    plt.ylabel("Cumulative Return")
    plt.grid(True)

    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# %matplotlib inline  

import time
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pycoingecko import CoinGeckoAPI

# ========= Settings =========
COINS = ["bitcoin", "ethereum", "tether", "dogecoin", "shiba-inu", "litecoin"]
TICKER = {
    "bitcoin":"BTC","ethereum":"ETH","tether":"USDT",
    "dogecoin":"DOGE","shiba-inu":"SHIB","litecoin":"LTC"
}
VS = "usd"
DAYS = 365
SLEEP = 0.9

# Momentum & risk settings
MOM_LB = 60        # ROC lookback (days)
VOL_LB = 30        # rolling window for mean/vol
REB_DAYS = 7       # rebalance every 7 days
TARGET_ANN_VOL = 0.20
TRADING_DAYS = 365

# Costs per rebalance turnover (sum |w|)
COST_MARKET = 0.0020   # 20 bps (20 slippage)
COST_LIMIT  = 0.0007   # 7  bps commission
# ===========================

cg = CoinGeckoAPI()

def fetch_close_series(coin_id, vs=VS, days=DAYS):
    """Return a daily close series for coin_id (handles API method names)."""
    try:
        mc = cg.get_coin_market_chart(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days)
    except AttributeError:
        mc = cg.get_coin_market_chart_by_id(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days)
    px = pd.DataFrame(mc["prices"], columns=["ts","close"])
    px["date"] = pd.to_datetime(px["ts"], unit="ms")
    s = px.set_index("date")["close"].sort_index()
    return s

# 1) Fetch closes & align daily
prices = {}
for c in COINS:
    print("Fetching", c, "...")
    s = fetch_close_series(c)
    time.sleep(SLEEP)
    prices[c] = s
prices = pd.DataFrame(prices).resample("1D").last().dropna(how="all").ffill()

# 2) Daily returns and indicators
rets = prices.pct_change().fillna(0.0)
roc  = prices.pct_change(MOM_LB)          # momentum signal
mu   = rets.rolling(VOL_LB).mean()        # mean daily return
sig  = rets.rolling(VOL_LB).std().replace(0, 1e-8)   # daily vol

# ---------- Weight builders (risky basket excludes USDT; USDT is buffer) ----------
def simplex_project(w):
    w = np.maximum(w, 0.0)
    s = w.sum()
    return (w / s) if s > 0 else w

def w_equal(row_roc, row_sig):
    elig = (row_roc > 0).astype(float); elig["tether"] = 0.0
    if elig.sum() == 0: return pd.Series(0.0, index=row_roc.index)
    return elig / elig.sum()

def w_vol_parity(row_roc, row_sig):
    elig = (row_roc > 0).astype(float); elig["tether"] = 0.0
    inv_vol = 1.0 / row_sig.replace(0, np.nan)
    w = (elig * inv_vol).fillna(0.0)
    w = simplex_project(w.values)
    return pd.Series(w, index=row_sig.index)

def w_sharpe(row_roc, row_mu, row_sig):
    elig = (row_roc > 0).astype(float); elig["tether"] = 0.0
    score = (row_mu.clip(lower=0) / row_sig.replace(0, np.nan)).replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)
    w = (elig * score).fillna(0.0)
    w = simplex_project(w.values)
    return pd.Series(w, index=row_mu.index)

def w_signal_strength(row_roc):
    # weight  max(ROC, 0)
    score = row_roc.clip(lower=0.0)
    score["tether"] = 0.0
    w = simplex_project(score.values)
    return pd.Series(w, index=score.index)

# Vol targeting
def vol_target_scale(weights, cov):
    w = weights.values
    sigma_p = np.sqrt(max(0.0, w @ cov.values @ w))
    ann_vol = sigma_p * np.sqrt(TRADING_DAYS)
    if ann_vol == 0 or np.isnan(ann_vol):
        return 0.0
    return float(TARGET_ANN_VOL / ann_vol)

# Rebalance schedule
dates = rets.index
rebal_idx = np.arange(0, len(dates), REB_DAYS)

schemes = ["EW","VP","SW","SIG"]
builders = {
    "EW": lambda roc_now, mu_win, sig_win, cov_win: w_equal(roc_now, sig_win),
    "VP": lambda roc_now, mu_win, sig_win, cov_win: w_vol_parity(roc_now, sig_win),
    "SW": lambda roc_now, mu_win, sig_win, cov_win: w_sharpe(roc_now, mu_win, sig_win),
    "SIG":lambda roc_now, mu_win, sig_win, cov_win: w_signal_strength(roc_now)
}

# Storage
eq_market = {k: pd.Series(index=dates, dtype=float) for k in schemes}
eq_limit  = {k: pd.Series(index=dates, dtype=float) for k in schemes}
w_timeline = {k: pd.DataFrame(0.0, index=dates, columns=COINS) for k in schemes}
turnover = {k: 0.0 for k in schemes}
prev_w   = {k: pd.Series(0.0, index=COINS) for k in schemes}

# Init equity
for k in schemes:
    eq_market[k].iloc[0] = 1.0
    eq_limit[k].iloc[0]  = 1.0
    w_timeline[k].iloc[0] = prev_w[k].values

# ---------- Run backtest ----------
for i, dt in enumerate(dates):
    # Update equity using yesterday's weights
    if i > 0:
        r = rets.loc[dt]
        for k in schemes:
            port_r = float(np.nan_to_num((prev_w[k] * r).sum()))
            eq_market[k].iloc[i] = eq_market[k].iloc[i-1] * (1 + port_r)
            eq_limit[k].iloc[i]  = eq_limit[k].iloc[i-1]  * (1 + port_r)
            w_timeline[k].iloc[i] = prev_w[k].values

    # Rebalance
    if i in rebal_idx and i > 0:
        start = max(0, i - VOL_LB)
        window_dates = dates[start:i]
        if len(window_dates) < max(5, VOL_LB//2):
            continue

        mu_win  = rets.loc[window_dates].mean()
        cov_win = rets.loc[window_dates].cov().fillna(0.0)
        sig_win = rets.loc[window_dates].std().replace(0, 1e-8)
        roc_now = roc.loc[dt].fillna(0.0)

        for k, builder in builders.items():
            # raw risky weights from builder
            w_risky = builder(roc_now.copy(), mu_win.copy(), sig_win.copy(), cov_win.copy())
            # exclude USDT from risky basket (it is the buffer)
            risky_vec = w_risky.copy(); risky_vec["tether"] = 0.0
            # vol target scaling
            scale = vol_target_scale(risky_vec, cov_win.loc[risky_vec.index, risky_vec.index]) if risky_vec.sum()>0 else 0.0
            risky_scaled = risky_vec * scale
            # residual to USDT
            usdt_w = max(0.0, 1.0 - risky_scaled.sum())
            w_final = risky_scaled.copy(); w_final["tether"] = usdt_w
            w_final = w_final.reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)

            # turnover & costs today
            w_prev = prev_w[k].reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)
            t = float((w_final - w_prev).abs().sum())
            turnover[k] += t
            eq_market[k].iloc[i] *= (1 - t * COST_MARKET)
            eq_limit[k].iloc[i]  *= (1 - t * COST_LIMIT)

            prev_w[k] = w_final
            w_timeline[k].iloc[i] = w_final.values

# Forward-fill equities & weights
for k in schemes:
    eq_market[k] = eq_market[k].ffill()
    eq_limit[k]  = eq_limit[k].ffill()
    w_timeline[k] = w_timeline[k].ffill()

# ---------- Metrics ----------
def perf_metrics(eq):
    eq = eq.dropna()
    if len(eq) < 10:
        return dict(CAGR=np.nan, AnnVol=np.nan, Sharpe=np.nan, MaxDD=np.nan)
    total_days = (eq.index[-1] - eq.index[0]).days or len(eq)
    cagr = eq.iloc[-1]**(365/total_days) - 1.0
    er = eq.pct_change().dropna()
    ann_vol = er.std() * np.sqrt(365)
    sharpe = (cagr / ann_vol) if ann_vol and not np.isnan(ann_vol) and ann_vol!=0 else np.nan
    peak = eq.cummax()
    dd = eq/peak - 1.0
    maxdd = dd.min()
    return dict(CAGR=cagr, AnnVol=ann_vol, Sharpe=sharpe, MaxDD=maxdd)

rows = []
for k in schemes:
    m = perf_metrics(eq_market[k])
    l = perf_metrics(eq_limit[k])
    rows.append({
        "Scheme": k,
        "CAGR (Market %)": round(m["CAGR"]*100, 2),
        "AnnVol (Market %)": round(m["AnnVol"]*100, 2) if not np.isnan(m["AnnVol"]) else np.nan,
        "Sharpe (Market)": round(m["Sharpe"], 2) if not np.isnan(m["Sharpe"]) else np.nan,
        "MaxDD (Market %)": round(m["MaxDD"]*100, 2) if not np.isnan(m["MaxDD"]) else np.nan,
        "CAGR (Limit %)": round(l["CAGR"]*100, 2),
        "AnnVol (Limit %)": round(l["AnnVol"]*100, 2) if not np.isnan(l["AnnVol"]) else np.nan,
        "Sharpe (Limit)": round(l["Sharpe"], 2) if not np.isnan(l["Sharpe"]) else np.nan,
        "MaxDD (Limit %)": round(l["MaxDD"]*100, 2) if not np.isnan(l["MaxDD"]) else np.nan,
        "Turnover (|w|)": round(turnover[k], 2)
    })
metrics = pd.DataFrame(rows).set_index("Scheme").sort_values("CAGR (Market %)", ascending=False)
print("\n=== Momentum Weighting  Performance Summary (1Y) ===")
print(metrics)

# ---------- Equity Curves ----------
plt.figure(figsize=(13,6))
for k in schemes:
    plt.plot(eq_market[k].index, eq_market[k].values, label=f"{k} (Market)")
    plt.plot(eq_limit[k].index,  eq_limit[k].values,  linestyle="--", label=f"{k} (Limit)")
plt.title("Equity Curves  Momentum Weighting (Market solid / Limit dashed)")
plt.ylabel("Equity (Start=1.0)")
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.4)
plt.legend(ncol=2, fontsize=9)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# ---------- Final Return Bar Chart ----------
final_bar = pd.DataFrame({
    "Market": [ (eq_market[k].iloc[-1]-1)*100 for k in schemes ],
    "Limit":  [ (eq_limit[k].iloc[-1]-1)*100  for k in schemes ]
}, index=schemes)

ax = final_bar.plot(kind="bar", figsize=(10,5), width=0.8)
plt.title("Final 1Y Return (%)  Market vs Limit Costs")

import time
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pycoingecko import CoinGeckoAPI

# ---------------- Settings ----------------
COINS   = ["bitcoin", "ethereum", "dogecoin", "shiba-inu", "tether"]  # USDT as buffer/cash
TICKER  = {"bitcoin":"BTC","ethereum":"ETH","dogecoin":"DOGE","shiba-inu":"SHIB","tether":"USDT"}
VS      = "usd"
DAYS    = 365
SLEEP   = 0.6

REV_LOOKBACK = 1     # 1-day reversal signal (set 2-5 for multi-day)
VOL_WIN      = 30    # rolling window for vol (and mu) estimates
REB_DAYS     = 7     # weekly rebalance
TRADING_DAYS = 365   # CoinGecko is calendar-daily

COST_MARKET = 0.0020 # 20 bps per unit turnover (market orders)
COST_LIMIT  = 0.0007 # 7 bps per unit turnover (limit orders)

BENCHMARK = "bitcoin"  # for alpha/beta
# ------------------------------------------

cg = CoinGeckoAPI()

def fetch_close_series(coin_id, vs=VS, days=DAYS):
    data = cg.get_coin_market_chart_by_id(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days, interval="daily")
    px = pd.DataFrame(data["prices"], columns=["ts","close"])
    px["date"] = pd.to_datetime(px["ts"], unit="ms", utc=True).dt.tz_convert("UTC")
    return px.set_index("date")["close"].sort_index()

# 1) Data
prices = {}
for c in COINS:
    prices[c] = fetch_close_series(c); time.sleep(SLEEP)
prices = pd.DataFrame(prices).resample("1D").last().ffill().dropna(how="all")
rets   = prices.pct_change().dropna()

# 2) Reversal inputs (info available at t to set weights for t)
prior_ret = rets.shift(REV_LOOKBACK).iloc[REV_LOOKBACK:]
vol_roll  = rets.rolling(VOL_WIN).std().replace(0, np.nan).iloc[REV_LOOKBACK:]
mu_roll   = rets.rolling(VOL_WIN).mean().iloc[REV_LOOKBACK:]

# ---------- Helpers ----------
def simplex_project(w):
    w = np.maximum(w, 0.0)
    s = w.sum()
    return w / s if s > 0 else w

def perf_metrics_from_returns(r, bench=None, periods_per_year=TRADING_DAYS):
    r = r.dropna()
    if len(r) < 5:  # guard
        return dict(AnnReturn=np.nan, AnnVol=np.nan, Sharpe=np.nan, MaxDD=np.nan, Alpha=np.nan, Beta=np.nan)

    # Annualized return (CAGR from returns)
    ann_ret = (1 + r).prod() ** (periods_per_year / len(r)) - 1
    ann_vol = r.std() * np.sqrt(periods_per_year)
    sharpe  = (ann_ret / ann_vol) if (ann_vol and not np.isnan(ann_vol) and ann_vol != 0) else np.nan

    # Max drawdown
    curve  = (1 + r).cumprod()
    max_dd = (curve / curve.cummax() - 1.0).min()

    alpha = np.nan; beta = np.nan
    if bench is not None:
        df = pd.concat([r, bench.loc[r.index]], axis=1).dropna()
        if len(df) > 5 and df.iloc[:,1].var() > 0:
            cov  = np.cov(df.iloc[:,0], df.iloc[:,1])
            beta = cov[0,1] / cov[1,1]
            bench_ann = (1 + df.iloc[:,1]).prod() ** (periods_per_year / len(df)) - 1
            alpha = ann_ret - beta * bench_ann

    return dict(AnnReturn=ann_ret, AnnVol=ann_vol, Sharpe=sharpe, MaxDD=max_dd, Alpha=alpha, Beta=beta)

# ---------- Reversal strategies (USDT excluded from risky bucket) ----------
def w_equal_reversal(row_prior):
    elig = (row_prior < 0).astype(float)  # prior losers only
    elig["tether"] = 0.0
    if elig.sum() == 0:
        return pd.Series(0.0, index=row_prior.index)
    return (elig / elig.sum())

def w_vol_parity_reversal(row_prior, row_vol):
    elig = (row_prior < 0).astype(float); elig["tether"] = 0.0
    inv_vol = 1.0 / row_vol.replace(0, np.nan)
    w = (elig * inv_vol).fillna(0.0)
    return pd.Series(simplex_project(w.values), index=row_prior.index)

def w_sharpe_reversal(row_prior, row_mu, row_vol):
    # Sharpe Ratio Weighting among prior losers: weight  (mu/vol)
    elig = (row_prior < 0).astype(float); elig["tether"] = 0.0
    score = (row_mu.clip(lower=0) / row_vol.replace(0, np.nan)).replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)
    w = (elig * score).fillna(0.0)
    return pd.Series(simplex_project(w.values), index=row_prior.index)

def w_signal_strength_reversal(row_prior):
    # Proportional to magnitude of prior loss
    score = (-row_prior).clip(lower=0.0); score["tether"] = 0.0
    return pd.Series(simplex_project(score.values), index=score.index)

builders = {
    "REV_EQ":  lambda pr, mu, vol: w_equal_reversal(pr),
    "REV_VP":  lambda pr, mu, vol: w_vol_parity_reversal(pr, vol),
    "REV_SW":  lambda pr, mu, vol: w_sharpe_reversal(pr, mu, vol),  # << Sharpe Ratio Weighting
    "REV_SIG": lambda pr, mu, vol: w_signal_strength_reversal(pr),
}

# 3) Backtest (weekly rebal; costs on turnover)
dates     = prior_ret.index
rebal_idx = set(dates[::REB_DAYS])
bench_ret = rets[BENCHMARK]

results = {}
equity_mkt = {}
equity_lim = {}
weights_ts = {}

for name, build in builders.items():
    eq_m = pd.Series(index=dates, dtype=float)
    eq_l = pd.Series(index=dates, dtype=float)
    eq_m.iloc[0] = 1.0; eq_l.iloc[0] = 1.0
    w_prev = pd.Series(0.0, index=COINS)
    W = pd.DataFrame(0.0, index=dates, columns=COINS)

    for i, dt in enumerate(dates):
        # Daily P&L with yesterday's weights
        if i > 0:
            r = rets.loc[dt].reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)
            port_r = float((w_prev * r).sum())
            eq_m.iloc[i] = eq_m.iloc[i-1] * (1 + port_r)
            eq_l.iloc[i] = eq_l.iloc[i-1] * (1 + port_r)
            W.iloc[i] = w_prev.values

        # Rebalance (apply turnover costs)
        if (dt in rebal_idx) and (i > 0):
            pr  = prior_ret.loc[dt].reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)
            mu  = mu_roll.loc[dt].reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)
            vol = vol_roll.loc[dt].reindex(COINS).replace(0, np.nan)

            w_raw  = build(pr.copy(), mu.copy(), vol.copy())
            risky  = w_raw.copy(); risky["tether"] = 0.0
            risky  = risky / risky.sum() if risky.sum() > 0 else risky
            usdt_w = max(0.0, 1.0 - risky.sum())
            w_new  = risky.copy(); w_new["tether"] = usdt_w
            w_new  = w_new.reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)

            t = float((w_new - w_prev).abs().sum())   # turnover = |w|
            eq_m.iloc[i] *= (1 - t * COST_MARKET)
            eq_l.iloc[i] *= (1 - t * COST_LIMIT)
            w_prev = w_new
            W.iloc[i] = w_prev.values

# %matplotlib inline  

import time
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pycoingecko import CoinGeckoAPI

# ========= Settings =========
COINS = ["bitcoin", "ethereum", "tether", "dogecoin", "shiba-inu", "litecoin"]
TICKER = {
    "bitcoin":"BTC","ethereum":"ETH","tether":"USDT",
    "dogecoin":"DOGE","shiba-inu":"SHIB","litecoin":"LTC"
}
VS = "usd"
DAYS = 365
SLEEP = 0.9

# Momentum & risk settings
MOM_LB = 60        # ROC lookback (days)
VOL_LB = 30        # rolling window for mean/vol
REB_DAYS = 7       # rebalance every 7 days
TARGET_ANN_VOL = 0.20
TRADING_DAYS = 365

# Costs per rebalance turnover (sum |w|)
COST_MARKET = 0.0020   # 20 bps
COST_LIMIT  = 0.0007   # 7  bps

# Benchmark for Alpha/Beta (daily returns). Use "bitcoin" or any in COINS.
BENCHMARK_COIN = "bitcoin"
# ===========================

cg = CoinGeckoAPI()

def fetch_close_series(coin_id, vs=VS, days=DAYS):
    """Return a daily close series for coin_id (handles API method names)."""
    try:
        mc = cg.get_coin_market_chart(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days)
    except AttributeError:
        mc = cg.get_coin_market_chart_by_id(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days)
    px = pd.DataFrame(mc["prices"], columns=["ts","close"])
    px["date"] = pd.to_datetime(px["ts"], unit="ms")
    s = px.set_index("date")["close"].sort_index()
    return s

# 1) Fetch closes & align daily
prices = {}
for c in COINS:
    print("Fetching", c, "...")
    s = fetch_close_series(c)
    time.sleep(SLEEP)
    prices[c] = s
prices = pd.DataFrame(prices).resample("1D").last().dropna(how="all").ffill()

# 2) Daily returns and indicators
rets = prices.pct_change().fillna(0.0)
roc  = prices.pct_change(MOM_LB)
mu   = rets.rolling(VOL_LB).mean()
sig  = rets.rolling(VOL_LB).std().replace(0, 1e-8)

# ---------- Weight builders (risky basket excludes USDT; USDT is buffer) ----------
def simplex_project(w):
    w = np.maximum(w, 0.0)
    s = w.sum()
    return (w / s) if s > 0 else w

def w_equal(row_roc, row_sig):
    elig = (row_roc > 0).astype(float); elig["tether"] = 0.0
    if elig.sum() == 0: return pd.Series(0.0, index=row_roc.index)
    return elig / elig.sum()

def w_vol_parity(row_roc, row_sig):
    elig = (row_roc > 0).astype(float); elig["tether"] = 0.0
    inv_vol = 1.0 / row_sig.replace(0, np.nan)
    w = (elig * inv_vol).fillna(0.0)
    w = simplex_project(w.values)
    return pd.Series(w, index=row_sig.index)

def w_sharpe(row_roc, row_mu, row_sig):
    elig = (row_roc > 0).astype(float); elig["tether"] = 0.0
    score = (row_mu.clip(lower=0) / row_sig.replace(0, np.nan)).replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)
    w = (elig * score).fillna(0.0)
    w = simplex_project(w.values)
    return pd.Series(w, index=row_mu.index)

def w_signal_strength(row_roc):
    score = row_roc.clip(lower=0.0)
    score["tether"] = 0.0
    w = simplex_project(score.values)
    return pd.Series(w, index=score.index)

# Vol targeting
def vol_target_scale(weights, cov):
    w = weights.values
    sigma_p = np.sqrt(max(0.0, w @ cov.values @ w))
    ann_vol = sigma_p * np.sqrt(TRADING_DAYS)
    if ann_vol == 0 or np.isnan(ann_vol):
        return 0.0
    return float(TARGET_ANN_VOL / ann_vol)

# Rebalance schedule
dates = rets.index
rebal_idx = np.arange(0, len(dates), REB_DAYS)

schemes = ["EW","VP","SW","SIG"]
builders = {
    "EW": lambda roc_now, mu_win, sig_win, cov_win: w_equal(roc_now, sig_win),
    "VP": lambda roc_now, mu_win, sig_win, cov_win: w_vol_parity(roc_now, sig_win),
    "SW": lambda roc_now, mu_win, sig_win, cov_win: w_sharpe(roc_now, mu_win, sig_win),
    "SIG":lambda roc_now, mu_win, sig_win, cov_win: w_signal_strength(roc_now)
}

# Storage
eq_market = {k: pd.Series(index=dates, dtype=float) for k in schemes}
eq_limit  = {k: pd.Series(index=dates, dtype=float) for k in schemes}
w_timeline = {k: pd.DataFrame(0.0, index=dates, columns=COINS) for k in schemes}
turnover = {k: 0.0 for k in schemes}
prev_w   = {k: pd.Series(0.0, index=COINS) for k in schemes}

# Init equity
for k in schemes:
    eq_market[k].iloc[0] = 1.0
    eq_limit[k].iloc[0]  = 1.0
    w_timeline[k].iloc[0] = prev_w[k].values

# ---------- Run backtest ----------
for i, dt in enumerate(dates):
    # Update equity using yesterday's weights
    if i > 0:
        r = rets.loc[dt]
        for k in schemes:
            port_r = float(np.nan_to_num((prev_w[k] * r).sum()))
            eq_market[k].iloc[i] = eq_market[k].iloc[i-1] * (1 + port_r)
            eq_limit[k].iloc[i]  = eq_limit[k].iloc[i-1]  * (1 + port_r)
            w_timeline[k].iloc[i] = prev_w[k].values

    # Rebalance
    if i in rebal_idx and i > 0:
        start = max(0, i - VOL_LB)
        window_dates = dates[start:i]
        if len(window_dates) < max(5, VOL_LB//2):
            continue

        mu_win  = rets.loc[window_dates].mean()
        cov_win = rets.loc[window_dates].cov().fillna(0.0)
        sig_win = rets.loc[window_dates].std().replace(0, 1e-8)
        roc_now = roc.loc[dt].fillna(0.0)

        for k, builder in builders.items():
            # raw risky weights from builder
            w_risky = builder(roc_now.copy(), mu_win.copy(), sig_win.copy(), cov_win.copy())
            # exclude USDT from risky basket (it is the buffer)
            risky_vec = w_risky.copy(); risky_vec["tether"] = 0.0
            # vol target scaling
            scale = vol_target_scale(risky_vec, cov_win.loc[risky_vec.index, risky_vec.index]) if risky_vec.sum()>0 else 0.0
            risky_scaled = risky_vec * scale
            # residual to USDT
            usdt_w = max(0.0, 1.0 - risky_scaled.sum())
            w_final = risky_scaled.copy(); w_final["tether"] = usdt_w
            w_final = w_final.reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)

            # turnover & costs today
            w_prev = prev_w[k].reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)
            t = float((w_final - w_prev).abs().sum())
            turnover[k] += t
            eq_market[k].iloc[i] *= (1 - t * COST_MARKET)
            eq_limit[k].iloc[i]  *= (1 - t * COST_LIMIT)

            prev_w[k] = w_final
            w_timeline[k].iloc[i] = w_final.values

# Forward-fill equities & weights
for k in schemes:
    eq_market[k] = eq_market[k].ffill()
    eq_limit[k]  = eq_limit[k].ffill()
    w_timeline[k] = w_timeline[k].ffill()

# ---------- Metrics (incl. MaxDD, Alpha, Beta) ----------
def perf_metrics(eq):
    eq = eq.dropna()
    if len(eq) < 10:
        return dict(CAGR=np.nan, AnnVol=np.nan, Sharpe=np.nan, MaxDD=np.nan)
    total_days = (eq.index[-1] - eq.index[0]).days or len(eq)
    cagr = eq.iloc[-1]**(365/total_days) - 1.0
    er = eq.pct_change().dropna()
    ann_vol = er.std() * np.sqrt(365)
    sharpe = (cagr / ann_vol) if ann_vol and not np.isnan(ann_vol) and ann_vol!=0 else np.nan
    peak = eq.cummax()
    dd = eq/peak - 1.0
    maxdd = dd.min()
    return dict(CAGR=cagr, AnnVol=ann_vol, Sharpe=sharpe, MaxDD=maxdd)

# Benchmark daily returns (BTC by default)
bench_ret = rets[BENCHMARK_COIN].copy()
bench_ret = bench_ret.loc[bench_ret.index.intersection(dates)].fillna(0.0)

def alpha_beta(eq):
    """Daily CAPM-style alpha (annualized) and beta vs benchmark (risk-free ~ 0)."""
    y = eq.pct_change().dropna()
    x = bench_ret.loc[y.index]
    x = x.fillna(0.0)
    if len(y) < 10 or x.std() == 0:
        return np.nan, np.nan
    # OLS: y = a + b*x
    beta = np.cov(y, x)[0,1] / np.var(x)
    alpha_daily = y.mean() - beta * x.mean()
    alpha_annual = alpha_daily * 365.0  # small-return approximation
    return float(alpha_annual), float(beta)

rows = []
for k in schemes:
    m = perf_metrics(eq_market[k])
    l = perf_metrics(eq_limit[k])
    a_m, b_m = alpha_beta(eq_market[k])
    a_l, b_l = alpha_beta(eq_limit[k])
    rows.append({
        "Scheme": k,
        "CAGR (Market %)": round(m["CAGR"]*100, 2),
        "AnnVol (Market %)": round(m["AnnVol"]*100, 2) if not np.isnan(m["AnnVol"]) else np.nan,
        "Sharpe (Market)": round(m["Sharpe"], 2) if not np.isnan(m["Sharpe"]) else np.nan,
        "MaxDD (Market %)": round(m["MaxDD"]*100, 2) if not np.isnan(m["MaxDD"]) else np.nan,
        "Alpha (Market, %/yr)": round(a_m*100, 2) if not np.isnan(a_m) else np.nan,
        "Beta (Market vs BTC)": round(b_m, 2) if not np.isnan(b_m) else np.nan,
        "CAGR (Limit %)": round(l["CAGR"]*100, 2),
        "AnnVol (Limit %)": round(l["AnnVol"]*100, 2) if not np.isnan(l["AnnVol"]) else np.nan,
        "Sharpe (Limit)": round(l["Sharpe"], 2) if not np.isnan(l["Sharpe"]) else np.nan,
        "MaxDD (Limit %)": round(l["MaxDD"]*100, 2) if not np.isnan(l["MaxDD"]) else np.nan,
        "Alpha (Limit, %/yr)": round(a_l*100, 2) if not np.isnan(a_l) else np.nan,
        "Beta (Limit vs BTC)": round(b_l, 2) if not np.isnan(b_l) else np.nan,
        "Turnover (|w|)": round(turnover[k], 2)
    })
metrics = pd.DataFrame(rows).set_index("Scheme").sort_values("CAGR (Market %)", ascending=False)
print(f"\n=== Momentum Weighting  Performance Summary (1Y) vs Benchmark={TICKER[BENCHMARK_COIN]} ===")
print(metrics)

# ---------- Equity Curves ----------
plt.figure(figsize=(13,6))
for k in schemes:
    plt.plot(eq_market[k].index, eq_market[k].values, label=f"{k} (Market)")
    plt.plot(eq_limit[k].index,  eq_limit[k].values,  linestyle="--", label=f"{k} (Limit)")
plt.title("Equity Curves  Momentum Weighting (Market solid / Limit dashed)")

import time
import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from pycoingecko import CoinGeckoAPI

# ---------------- Settings ----------------
COINS   = ["bitcoin", "ethereum", "dogecoin", "shiba-inu", "tether"]  # USDT as buffer/cash
TICKER  = {"bitcoin":"BTC","ethereum":"ETH","dogecoin":"DOGE","shiba-inu":"SHIB","tether":"USDT"}
VS      = "usd"
DAYS    = 365
SLEEP   = 0.6

REV_LOOKBACK = 1     # 1-day reversal signal (set 2-5 for multi-day)
VOL_WIN      = 30    # rolling window for vol (and mu) estimates
REB_DAYS     = 7     # weekly rebalance
TRADING_DAYS = 365   # CoinGecko is calendar-daily

COST_MARKET = 0.0020 # 20 bps per unit turnover (market orders)
COST_LIMIT  = 0.0007 # 7 bps per unit turnover (limit orders)

BENCHMARK = "bitcoin"  # for alpha/beta
# ------------------------------------------

cg = CoinGeckoAPI()

def fetch_close_series(coin_id, vs=VS, days=DAYS):
    data = cg.get_coin_market_chart_by_id(id=coin_id, vs_currency=vs, days=days, interval="daily")
    px = pd.DataFrame(data["prices"], columns=["ts","close"])
    px["date"] = pd.to_datetime(px["ts"], unit="ms", utc=True).dt.tz_convert("UTC")
    return px.set_index("date")["close"].sort_index()

# 1) Data
prices = {}
for c in COINS:
    prices[c] = fetch_close_series(c); time.sleep(SLEEP)
prices = pd.DataFrame(prices).resample("1D").last().ffill().dropna(how="all")
rets   = prices.pct_change().dropna()

# 2) Reversal inputs (info available at t to set weights for t)
prior_ret = rets.shift(REV_LOOKBACK).iloc[REV_LOOKBACK:]
vol_roll  = rets.rolling(VOL_WIN).std().replace(0, np.nan).iloc[REV_LOOKBACK:]
mu_roll   = rets.rolling(VOL_WIN).mean().iloc[REV_LOOKBACK:]

# ---------- Helpers ----------
def simplex_project(w):
    w = np.maximum(w, 0.0)
    s = w.sum()
    return w / s if s > 0 else w

def perf_metrics_from_returns(r, bench=None, periods_per_year=TRADING_DAYS):
    r = r.dropna()
    if len(r) < 5:  # guard
        return dict(AnnReturn=np.nan, AnnVol=np.nan, Sharpe=np.nan, MaxDD=np.nan, Alpha=np.nan, Beta=np.nan)

    # Annualized return (CAGR from returns)
    ann_ret = (1 + r).prod() ** (periods_per_year / len(r)) - 1
    ann_vol = r.std() * np.sqrt(periods_per_year)
    sharpe  = (ann_ret / ann_vol) if (ann_vol and not np.isnan(ann_vol) and ann_vol != 0) else np.nan

    # Max drawdown
    curve  = (1 + r).cumprod()
    max_dd = (curve / curve.cummax() - 1.0).min()

    alpha = np.nan; beta = np.nan
    if bench is not None:
        df = pd.concat([r, bench.loc[r.index]], axis=1).dropna()
        if len(df) > 5 and df.iloc[:,1].var() > 0:
            cov  = np.cov(df.iloc[:,0], df.iloc[:,1])
            beta = cov[0,1] / cov[1,1]
            bench_ann = (1 + df.iloc[:,1]).prod() ** (periods_per_year / len(df)) - 1
            alpha = ann_ret - beta * bench_ann

    return dict(AnnReturn=ann_ret, AnnVol=ann_vol, Sharpe=sharpe, MaxDD=max_dd, Alpha=alpha, Beta=beta)

# ---------- Reversal strategies (USDT excluded from risky bucket) ----------
def w_equal_reversal(row_prior):
    elig = (row_prior < 0).astype(float)  # prior losers only
    elig["tether"] = 0.0
    if elig.sum() == 0:
        return pd.Series(0.0, index=row_prior.index)
    return (elig / elig.sum())

def w_vol_parity_reversal(row_prior, row_vol):
    elig = (row_prior < 0).astype(float); elig["tether"] = 0.0
    inv_vol = 1.0 / row_vol.replace(0, np.nan)
    w = (elig * inv_vol).fillna(0.0)
    return pd.Series(simplex_project(w.values), index=row_prior.index)

def w_sharpe_reversal(row_prior, row_mu, row_vol):
    # Sharpe Ratio Weighting among prior losers: weight  (mu/vol)
    elig = (row_prior < 0).astype(float); elig["tether"] = 0.0
    score = (row_mu.clip(lower=0) / row_vol.replace(0, np.nan)).replace([np.inf, -np.inf], np.nan)
    w = (elig * score).fillna(0.0)
    return pd.Series(simplex_project(w.values), index=row_prior.index)

def w_signal_strength_reversal(row_prior):
    # Proportional to magnitude of prior loss
    score = (-row_prior).clip(lower=0.0); score["tether"] = 0.0
    return pd.Series(simplex_project(score.values), index=score.index)

builders = {
    "REV_EQ":  lambda pr, mu, vol: w_equal_reversal(pr),
    "REV_VP":  lambda pr, mu, vol: w_vol_parity_reversal(pr, vol),
    "REV_SW":  lambda pr, mu, vol: w_sharpe_reversal(pr, mu, vol),  # << Sharpe Ratio Weighting
    "REV_SIG": lambda pr, mu, vol: w_signal_strength_reversal(pr),
}

# 3) Backtest (weekly rebal; costs on turnover)
dates     = prior_ret.index
rebal_idx = set(dates[::REB_DAYS])
bench_ret = rets[BENCHMARK]

results = {}
equity_mkt = {}
equity_lim = {}
weights_ts = {}

for name, build in builders.items():
    eq_m = pd.Series(index=dates, dtype=float)
    eq_l = pd.Series(index=dates, dtype=float)
    eq_m.iloc[0] = 1.0; eq_l.iloc[0] = 1.0
    w_prev = pd.Series(0.0, index=COINS)
    W = pd.DataFrame(0.0, index=dates, columns=COINS)

    for i, dt in enumerate(dates):
        # Daily P&L with yesterday's weights
        if i > 0:
            r = rets.loc[dt].reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)
            port_r = float((w_prev * r).sum())
            eq_m.iloc[i] = eq_m.iloc[i-1] * (1 + port_r)
            eq_l.iloc[i] = eq_l.iloc[i-1] * (1 + port_r)
            W.iloc[i] = w_prev.values

        # Rebalance (apply turnover costs)
        if (dt in rebal_idx) and (i > 0):
            pr  = prior_ret.loc[dt].reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)
            mu  = mu_roll.loc[dt].reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)
            vol = vol_roll.loc[dt].reindex(COINS).replace(0, np.nan)

            w_raw  = build(pr.copy(), mu.copy(), vol.copy())
            risky  = w_raw.copy(); risky["tether"] = 0.0
            risky  = risky / risky.sum() if risky.sum() > 0 else risky
            usdt_w = max(0.0, 1.0 - risky.sum())
            w_new  = risky.copy(); w_new["tether"] = usdt_w
            w_new  = w_new.reindex(COINS).fillna(0.0)

            t = float((w_new - w_prev).abs().sum())   # turnover = |w|
            eq_m.iloc[i] *= (1 - t * COST_MARKET)
            eq_l.iloc[i] *= (1 - t * COST_LIMIT)
            w_prev = w_new
            W.iloc[i] = w_prev.values

    equity_mkt[name] = eq_m.ffill()
    equity_lim[name] = eq_l.ffill()
    weights_ts[name] = W.ffill()

# 4) Metrics (per strategy, per cost model)
rows = []
for name in builders.keys():
    # daily returns from equity curves
    r_mkt = equity_mkt[name].pct_change().dropna()
    r_lim = equity_lim[name].pct_change().dropna()
    m_mkt = perf_metrics_from_returns(r_mkt, bench=bench_ret)
    m_lim = perf_metrics_from_returns(r_lim, bench=bench_ret)

    rows.append({
        "Strategy": name,
        "AnnReturn (MKT)": m_mkt["AnnReturn"],
        "AnnVol (MKT)": m_mkt["AnnVol"],
        "Sharpe (MKT)": m_mkt["Sharpe"],
        "MaxDD (MKT)": m_mkt["MaxDD"],
        "Alpha (MKT)": m_mkt["Alpha"],
        "Beta (MKT)": m_mkt["Beta"],
        "AnnReturn (LIM)": m_lim["AnnReturn"],
        "AnnVol (LIM)": m_lim["AnnVol"],
        "Sharpe (LIM)": m_lim["Sharpe"],
        "MaxDD (LIM)": m_lim["MaxDD"],
        "Alpha (LIM)": m_lim["Alpha"],
        "Beta (LIM)": m_lim["Beta"],
    })

report = pd.DataFrame(rows).set_index("Strategy")
print("\n=== Reversal Strategies  1Y Performance (vs BTC) ===")
print(report.round({
    "AnnReturn (MKT)":4, "AnnVol (MKT)":4, "Sharpe (MKT)":2, "MaxDD (MKT)":4, "Alpha (MKT)":4, "Beta (MKT)":2,
    "AnnReturn (LIM)":4, "AnnVol (LIM)":4, "Sharpe (LIM)":2, "MaxDD (LIM)":4, "Alpha (LIM)":4, "Beta (LIM)":2
}).sort_values("AnnReturn (MKT)", ascending=False))

# 5) Equity curves (market vs limit vs BTC)

for name in builders.keys():
    plt.plot(equity_mkt[name], label=f"{name} (MKT)")
    plt.plot(equity_lim[name], linestyle="--", label=f"{name} (LIM)")
plt.plot((1 + bench_ret.loc[equity_mkt[name].index]).cumprod(), color="black", linestyle=":", label=f"{TICKER[BENCHMARK]} Benchmark")
plt.title("Reversal Strategies  Equity Curves (Market solid / Limit dashed)")
plt.ylabel("Growth of $1")
plt.legend(ncol=2, fontsize=9)
plt.grid(True, alpha=0.4)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
